Sec. 103.004. DUTIES OF THE BOARD. (a) The board shall:
(1) advise the department on all matters relating to the
fund, including the fund's budget and the revenues necessary to
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 689 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

accomplish the purposes of the fund;
(2) advise the department in the adoption of rules relating
to the payment of claims from the fund and to the administration of
the fund; and
(3) conduct adjudicative hearings on disputed claims
presented for payment from the fund.
(b) The board shall develop and implement policies that provide
the public with a reasonable opportunity to appear before the board
and to speak on any issue under the jurisdiction of the board.
(c) The board shall develop and implement policies that clearly
separate the policymaking responsibilities of the board and the
management responsibilities of the commissioner and the staff of the
department.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1275, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 1995, 74th Leg., ch. 419, Sec. 1.22, eff. Sept. 1,
1995.

